<P>







<A NAME = "namis"><H2>NAMI'S LITERATURE COMMITTEE</H2></A><A HREF = "#top">[Return to Top]</A><br>



<P>



<strong>Why does NAMI have a Literature Committee?</strong>



<P>



The founding members of NAMI adopted three goals:  support for its



members, education of members and the general public, and advocacy



for research and better services.  The Literature Committee



was NAMI's first committee, and it was formed to implement the goal



of education.  The task of the committee was to identify



high-quality, non-technical books about serious mental illness, its



treatment and needed services, and to recommend them to NAMI



members and the public.  



